{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"RWLockProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"RWLockProtocol"}],"role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Protocol","symbolKind":"protocol","title":"RWLockProtocol","externalID":"s:4GLib14RWLockProtocolP"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The GRWLock struct is an opaque data structure to represent a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"reader-writer lock. It is similar to a "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" in that it allows","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"multiple threads to coordinate access to a shared resource.","type":"text"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"RWLockProtocol"},{"text":" : ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"PointerWrapper","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper","preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib14PointerWrapperP"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The difference to a mutex is that a reader-writer lock discriminates"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"between read-only (‘reader’) and full (‘writer’) access. While only","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"one thread at a time is allowed write access (by holding the ‘writer’"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"lock via ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_rw_lock_writer_lock()"},{"type":"text","text":"), multiple threads can gain"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"simultaneous read-only access (by holding the ‘reader’ lock via"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"g_rw_lock_reader_lock()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":")."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"It is unspecified whether readers or writers have priority in acquiring the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"lock when a reader already holds the lock and a writer is queued to acquire"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"it."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Here is an example for an array with access functions:","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"(C Language Example):"}]},{"syntax":"C","type":"codeListing","code":["  GRWLock lock;","  GPtrArray *array;","","  gpointer","  my_array_get (guint index)","  {","    gpointer retval = NULL;","","    if (!array)","      return NULL;","","    g_rw_lock_reader_lock (&lock);","    if (index < array->len)","      retval = g_ptr_array_index (array, index);","    g_rw_lock_reader_unlock (&lock);","","    return retval;","  }","","  void","  my_array_set (guint index, gpointer data)","  {","    g_rw_lock_writer_lock (&lock);","","    if (!array)","      array = g_ptr_array_new ();","","    if (index >= array->len)","      g_ptr_array_set_size (array, index+1);","    g_ptr_array_index (array, index) = data;","","    g_rw_lock_writer_unlock (&lock);","  }"," "]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This example shows an array which can be accessed by many readers","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"my_array_get()"},{"text":" function) simultaneously, whereas the writers","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"my_array_set()"},{"type":"text","text":" function) will only be allowed one at a time"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"and only if no readers currently access the array. This is because"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of the potentially dangerous resizing of the array. Using these"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"functions is fully multi-thread safe now.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If a "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RWLock","isActive":true},{"text":" is allocated in static storage then it can be used","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"without initialisation.  Otherwise, you should call"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_rw_lock_init()"},{"text":" on it and ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_rw_lock_clear()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" when done.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A GRWLock should only be accessed with the g_rw_lock_ functions.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RWLockProtocol","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol exposes the methods and properties of an underlying "},{"code":"GRWLock","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"The default implementation of these can be found in the protocol extension below.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"For a concrete class that implements these methods and properties, see ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RWLock","type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Alternatively, use "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RWLockRef","type":"reference"},{"text":" as a lighweight, ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"unowned"},{"text":" reference if you already have an instance you just want to use.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"sections":[],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RWLockProtocol"},"relationshipsSections":[{"title":"Inherits From","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper"],"kind":"relationships","type":"inheritsFrom"},{"type":"conformingTypes","title":"Conforming Types","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RWLock","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RWLockRef"],"kind":"relationships"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/rwlockprotocol"]}],"topicSections":[{"title":"Instance Methods","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RWLockProtocol\/clear()","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RWLockProtocol\/init_()","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RWLockProtocol\/readerLock()","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RWLockProtocol\/readerTrylock()","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RWLockProtocol\/readerUnlock()","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RWLockProtocol\/writerLock()","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RWLockProtocol\/writerTrylock()","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RWLockProtocol\/writerUnlock()"],"anchor":"Instance-Methods"}],"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/RWLockProtocol/readerTrylock()":{"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/rwlockprotocol\/readertrylock()","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"readerTrylock"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"text":"Bool","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"title":"readerTrylock()","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RWLockProtocol\/readerTrylock()","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Tries to obtain a read lock on "},{"code":"rwLock","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and returns "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"type":"text","text":" if"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the read lock was successfully obtained. Otherwise it","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"returns ","type":"text"},{"code":"false","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/Mutex":{"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/mutex","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Mutex","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex","isActive":true},{"text":" struct is an opaque data structure to represent a mutex","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"(mutual exclusion). It can be used to protect data against shared"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"access."}],"kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Mutex"}],"title":"Mutex"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/PointerWrapper":{"fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"PointerWrapper"}],"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Protocol for GLib types that wrap pointers.","type":"text"}],"title":"PointerWrapper","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/pointerwrapper","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"PointerWrapper"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper","type":"topic"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/RWLockProtocol/writerUnlock()":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RWLockProtocol\/writerUnlock()","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"writerUnlock"},{"text":"()","kind":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Release a write lock on "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"rwLock"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/rwlockprotocol\/writerunlock()","role":"symbol","title":"writerUnlock()","type":"topic"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/RWLockProtocol":{"fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"RWLockProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"RWLockProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The GRWLock struct is an opaque data structure to represent a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"reader-writer lock. It is similar to a "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex","isActive":true},{"text":" in that it allows","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"multiple threads to coordinate access to a shared resource.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/rwlockprotocol","type":"topic","title":"RWLockProtocol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RWLockProtocol"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/RWLockProtocol/writerLock()":{"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Obtain a write lock on "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"rwLock"},{"type":"text","text":". If another thread currently holds"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a read or write lock on "},{"code":"rwLock","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", the current thread will block","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"until all other threads have dropped their locks on "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"rwLock"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"writerLock"},{"kind":"text","text":"()"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RWLockProtocol\/writerLock()","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/rwlockprotocol\/writerlock()","title":"writerLock()"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/RWLockProtocol/writerTrylock()":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RWLockProtocol\/writerTrylock()","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"writerTrylock","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool"}],"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Tries to obtain a write lock on "},{"code":"rwLock","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". If another thread","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"currently holds a read or write lock on "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"rwLock"},{"type":"text","text":", it immediately"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"returns ","type":"text"},{"code":"false","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Otherwise it locks "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"rwLock"},{"type":"text","text":" and returns "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/rwlockprotocol\/writertrylock()","role":"symbol","title":"writerTrylock()","type":"topic"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/RWLockProtocol/readerUnlock()":{"kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"readerUnlock","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"()"}],"type":"topic","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RWLockProtocol\/readerUnlock()","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/rwlockprotocol\/readerunlock()","title":"readerUnlock()","abstract":[{"text":"Release a read lock on ","type":"text"},{"code":"rwLock","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/RWLockProtocol/clear()":{"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Frees the resources allocated to a lock with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_rw_lock_init()"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"clear"},{"text":"()","kind":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RWLockProtocol\/clear()","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/rwlockprotocol\/clear()","title":"clear()"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/RWLock":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"RWLock","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"RWLock","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RWLock","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The GRWLock struct is an opaque data structure to represent a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"reader-writer lock. It is similar to a ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" in that it allows"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"multiple threads to coordinate access to a shared resource."}],"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/rwlock","kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"RWLock"}]},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","title":"GLib","kind":"symbol","role":"collection","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glib","abstract":[]},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/RWLockProtocol/readerLock()":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RWLockProtocol\/readerLock()","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"readerLock"},{"kind":"text","text":"()"}],"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Obtain a read lock on "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"rwLock"},{"type":"text","text":". If another thread currently holds"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the write lock on "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"rwLock"},{"type":"text","text":", the current thread will block until the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"write lock was (held and) released. If another thread does not hold","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the write lock, but is waiting for it, it is implementation defined"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"whether the reader or writer will block. Read locks can be taken"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"recursively.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/rwlockprotocol\/readerlock()","role":"symbol","title":"readerLock()","type":"topic"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/RWLockProtocol/init_()":{"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Initializes a ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RWLock","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" so that it can be used."}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"init_"},{"kind":"text","text":"()"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RWLockProtocol\/init_()","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/rwlockprotocol\/init_()","title":"init_()"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/RWLockRef":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The GRWLock struct is an opaque data structure to represent a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"reader-writer lock. It is similar to a "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" in that it allows","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"multiple threads to coordinate access to a shared resource.","type":"text"}],"title":"RWLockRef","type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"RWLockRef","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/rwlockref","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RWLockRef","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"RWLockRef","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol"}}}